[
    {
        "content": "<p>one situation that came up in <a class=\"stream-topic\" data-stream-id=\"347488\" href=\"/#narrow/stream/347488-roctoberfest/topic/Show.20and.20Tell\">#roctoberfest &gt; Show and Tell</a>  is that this doesn't work that way it looks like it would:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nv\">lines</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"nf\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">List</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">map</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">\\</span><span class=\"nv\">line</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Str</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">split</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">line</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\",\"</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"nf\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">List</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">walk</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">...</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>this gets parsed as:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nv\">lines</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"nf\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">List</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">map</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nf\">\\</span><span class=\"nv\">line</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Str</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">split</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">line</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\",\"</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"nf\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">List</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">walk</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">...</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>...because the parser doesn't have a reason to believe the <code>\\line -&gt;</code> lambda was supposed to have ended before the <code>|&gt; List.walk</code></p>",
        "id": 301900229,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1664694694
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>however, we could change that</p>",
        "id": 301900311,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1664694743
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>if we introduced a rule that lambda bodies had to be indented, then this would Just Work the way it looks like it would:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nv\">lines</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"nf\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">List</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">map</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">\\</span><span class=\"nv\">line</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Str</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">split</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">line</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\",\"</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"nf\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">List</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">walk</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">...</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>that would be because <code>|&gt; List.walk</code> is outdented relative to the beginning of the <code>\\line -&gt;</code> lambda, which would signal that the lambda had ended</p>",
        "id": 301900348,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1664694799
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I can think of some downsides to this design:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>It would introduce another place in the language where indentation is significant (currently it's only significant in defs, in backpassing, and in <code>when</code>)</li>\n<li>It would mean you could no longer write something like this:</li>\n</ol>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nv\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">\\</span><span class=\"nv\">nums</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"kt\">List</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">map</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">nums</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">\\</span><span class=\"nv\">num</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nv\">num</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>...because that would be a syntax error. Instead, you would have to indent the last line, like so:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nv\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">\\</span><span class=\"nv\">nums</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"kt\">List</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">map</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">nums</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">\\</span><span class=\"nv\">num</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"nv\">num</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 301900511,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1664694958
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>granted, the latter is how the formatter would format it anyway today, but it's worth noting that neither of them would currently be a syntax error, whereas if we made lambdas require indentation, then only one of them would even parse</p>",
        "id": 301900572,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1664695004
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm curious what others think of this idea!</p>",
        "id": 301900582,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1664695012
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I am definitely pro indentation. I do it anyway for readability</p>",
        "id": 301900712,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1664695120
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think this example is just worse form of backpassing. As such, i think if you want that tabbing, you should just use backpassing.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nv\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">\\</span><span class=\"nv\">nums</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"kt\">List</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">map</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">nums</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">\\</span><span class=\"nv\">num</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nv\">num</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 301901055,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1664695491
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>yeah I don't think there's a compelling reason to support that</p>",
        "id": 301901302,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1664695712
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>it's more like \"if someone writes it by accident, do they get a syntax error or does it Just Work and then the formatter indents it for them as a matter of style\"</p>",
        "id": 301901312,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1664695730
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I consider it a very minor downside, but it is a downside nontheless <span aria-label=\"big smile\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f604\" role=\"img\" title=\"big smile\">:big_smile:</span></p>",
        "id": 301901328,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1664695748
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yeah, backpassing seems to alleviate any downside to this proposal...</p>",
        "id": 301902579,
        "sender_full_name": "jan kili",
        "timestamp": 1664696890
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>If we make bad indentation a syntax error here, then let's try to also mention the likely cause in the message</p>",
        "id": 301932901,
        "sender_full_name": "Brian Carroll",
        "timestamp": 1664715861
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Pro-indentation!</p>\n<p>To hell with those what want to bring named variables out of its scope!</p>",
        "id": 301944864,
        "sender_full_name": "Zeljko Nesic",
        "timestamp": 1664723141
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>For posterity (for anyone who finds these ideas threads and wonders which direction we went), could someone confirm if we made this change? It seems like we did, but I'm not sure.</p>\n<p>It might be nice to have a one-liner \"Accepted\" or \"Declined\" or whatever when we come to a decision, in order to bring closure to the conversation ;)</p>",
        "id": 314947971,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Gillette",
        "timestamp": 1670608136
    }
]